WEBVTT

00:02.302 --> 00:05.430
 Work at a hospital long enough,
you get used to anything.

00:05.505 --> 00:10.169
Whether it's Dr. Kim, who makes patients
take their pants off no matter what...

00:10.243 --> 00:12.177
Yep, you've got pink eye.

00:12.245 --> 00:14.213
Can I put my pants back on?

00:14.280 --> 00:16.043
Right after I put some drops in.

00:17.417 --> 00:20.580
Or nobody remembering
Ray Ketay's 80th birthday.

00:20.653 --> 00:22.985
Why aren't you making
a bigger fuss?

00:23.056 --> 00:25.115
Uh, I would have, Mr. Ketay,

00:25.191 --> 00:29.355
but Dr. Reid is throwing a huge
celebration for you later.

00:29.429 --> 00:31.397
 I should tell her about that.

00:31.464 --> 00:35.366
Truth is, thanks to modern medicine,
80 isn't that big a deal anymore.

00:35.435 --> 00:36.993
It's not like the olden days.

00:37.704 --> 00:42.004
Let us not feel sorrow for Bobby Adams.

00:42.075 --> 00:45.135
He was 12. He led a full life.

00:45.211 --> 00:47.111
He will be missed.

00:47.180 --> 00:50.240
Especially by his
beautiful wife, Jenny,

00:50.316 --> 00:53.683
who stood by him,
even when he turned six,

00:53.753 --> 00:54.913
had a midlife crisis,

00:55.021 --> 00:58.582
and was caught banging one of those
naked people that brought us corn.

00:59.292 --> 01:02.591
I'd be the oldest man
in Pilgrim Village.

01:02.662 --> 01:05.187
 Still, you should
always celebrate life

01:05.265 --> 01:08.200
because you never know when
it will throw you a curveball.

01:08.268 --> 01:09.826
Like with Dr. Cox.

01:09.903 --> 01:12.736
He recently made a decision
any doctor would have made,

01:12.806 --> 01:15.570
and because of it,
three patients died.

01:17.644 --> 01:20.306
At first, he was inconsolably sad.

01:23.183 --> 01:25.708
After that, he started acting out.

01:30.523 --> 01:34.015
In his defense, he did ask
for dressing on the side.

01:34.461 --> 01:36.224
Daphne!

01:37.831 --> 01:40.493
I heard that he attacked
one of the busboys.

01:40.567 --> 01:43.127
Yeah, I heard he
bitchslapped the maitre d'.

01:43.236 --> 01:46.000
Enough, gang.
That's how rumors get started.

01:46.072 --> 01:48.768
Gloria, I made a joke that
you hooked up with Leonard,

01:48.842 --> 01:52.608
the security guard with the hookhand,
now everyone thinks it's true.

01:52.679 --> 01:56.206
It is true. And I'm never going back.

01:56.282 --> 01:58.147
Gloria!

01:59.452 --> 02:01.386
I love me some white meat.

02:02.222 --> 02:06.522
OK... well, make sure you put
antiseptic on any puncture wounds, OK?

02:06.593 --> 02:10.154
Now I know Dr. Cox seems
crazy mad at the world right now,

02:10.263 --> 02:12.629
but let's remember,
three patients died.

02:12.732 --> 02:15.292
What's amazing is that
he can take a hit like that,

02:15.401 --> 02:17.665
one that would knock any of us
out for good,

02:17.737 --> 02:19.671
and come out still standing.

02:19.739 --> 02:22.902
That's why the man's an inspiration.
I mean, he is a rock.

02:23.009 --> 02:25.910
 Yep, he's the best damn doctor here.

02:25.979 --> 02:29.346
Newbie, give me a little trouble?
I'm having some help here.

02:29.449 --> 02:30.609
Oh, no.

02:31.384 --> 02:34.842
# I can't do this all on my own

02:34.921 --> 02:38.482
# No, I know I'm no Superman

02:41.427 --> 02:43.361
# I'm no Superman #

02:45.031 --> 02:47.158
All right, people, listen up.

02:47.233 --> 02:48.791
We are a family.

02:48.902 --> 02:51.871
And what do families do when
one of their own is in trouble?

02:51.938 --> 02:55.806
When my brother came out of the closet
my parents sent him to hetero camp.

02:55.875 --> 02:57.740
Families not from Connecticut.

02:57.810 --> 03:00.973
 Pregnancy had made Carla
a little hormonal.

03:01.047 --> 03:04.175
Dr. Kelso, I asked you to keep this
matter away from the Board.

03:04.250 --> 03:06.480
 Were you able to?
 Nurse Espinosa, I...

03:06.553 --> 03:08.521
 Were you?!
 Yes!

03:08.621 --> 03:12.785
I told them Dr. Cox was taking a leave
of absence due to problems at home.

03:12.892 --> 03:15.588
 Should anyone ask, you beat him.
 Beat him. Got it.

03:15.662 --> 03:18.130
I couldn't believe
how depressed he was.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.166
 It was so sad.
 Oh, I know.

03:20.233 --> 03:23.100
When I first heard about it,
I was like, "Whoa, no way."

03:23.169 --> 03:27.333
 You don't know what this is about.
 Sure, I do, donkeyboy up in ICU.

03:27.440 --> 03:29.374
We're talking about Dr. Cox.

03:29.442 --> 03:33.606
Oh. Well, if anyone's interested,
there's a donkeyboy in the ICU.

03:33.713 --> 03:35.977
 Baby?
 No, Turk.

03:36.049 --> 03:38.711
Now, Dr. Cox needs our help
getting through this.

03:38.785 --> 03:42.050
Jordan can watch him at morning
and at night, but she's got Jack.

03:42.121 --> 03:45.352
 She's not that emotionally available.
 I'm dead inside.

03:45.425 --> 03:47.723
We're all going
to spend time with him.

03:47.794 --> 03:50.228
I've made up a schedule.
I have the first shift.

03:50.296 --> 03:53.197
 Any questions? Meeting is adjourned.
 Oh.

03:53.933 --> 03:55.958
 Gosh!
 What?

03:56.035 --> 03:59.095
For God's sakes, Reid,
there's a donkeyboy upstairs.

